The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: State-run oil firms have hiked aviation turbine fuel price by 6.5 per cent in step with hardening global rates. In Delhi, ATF price was increased by Rs 2,519.83 per kilolitre to Rs 4,1216.43 effective from midnight. Major carriers said they would take a decision on raising fares in a couple of days.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: The petroleum ministry plans to approach Prime Minister Manmohan Singh soon as the finance ministry has promised to pay only Rs 12,000 crore to partly compensate state-run fuel retailers for the losses incurred for selling LPG and kerosene below market prices.                            
	 Washington, Jan. 15: The International Monetary Fund said the global economy was recovering faster than expected but growth continued to be fragile as many developed nations were dependent on government stimulus. Goldman Sachs said India was likely to grow 8.2 per cent in the next fiscal.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: Sebi has asked Societe Generale to explain why its registration in India should not be cancelled for providing wrong information on issuance of a financial instrument which enabled the overseas entity to invest in R-Com shares.                                                                                                                          
